The 2nd Annual Single Family Aggregation Strategies: The REO-to-Rental Forum






































































The 2nd Annual Single Family Aggregation Strategies: The REO-to-Rental Forum
Scottsdale, AZ

                                                                        December 4-6, 2013
                                                            






 Description
             Agenda 
             Event Contacts 
             Venue 
             Hotels 
             Sponsors 
            








The conference

            IMN is looking forward to being back in Scottsdale for our 2nd Annual Single Family Aggregation Strategies: The REO-to-Rental Forum December4-6. This forum will again promise to discuss the latest strategies and management intricacies of Institutional-level Investment in the $17 Billion single family buy-to-rental market as well as how Banks, Home Builders and other owners are dealing with their portfolio of foreclosed and vacant properties.The Top 10 Reasons You Need To Register For IMN's Single Family Aggregation/REO-to-Rental Forum:10. 800+ attended our Spring Florida event9. The added third day so even more networking, networking and networking8. The publics are coming.. the publics are coming...Dont miss the President/CEO panel with American Residential Properties, Beazer Pre-OwnedRental Homes, Reven Housing REIT and Waypoint7. What about that Blackstone securitzation6. New York expected weather: high 45 degrees, Phoenix: 65 degrees5. 28 individual sessions with 118 speakers4. Our first golf tournament3. The fund panel will include GTIS, Hyperion/Raineri, Pathfinder Partners and Sylvan Road 2. 50+ exhibitors/sponsors from the brokerage, economic/analytics,insurance, investment banking, legal, lending, property preservation/managementand other providers of services1. 55+ PE/Hedge Funds, Investors & NPL Buyers speakingWe look forward to seeing you there, December 4.

Who should attend

            Private Equity, REITs, Institutional Investors, Local & Federal Government Housing, Not-for-Profit Housing and Banks
        



Wednesday, December 4th, 2013


1:57 AM  Registration opens... Breakfast is served Courtesy of: 









1:57 AM  IMN Opening Remarks 





1:57 AM  The Macro Economy, the Housing Markets and the Single Family Rental Unit 


                            • New housing construction update • Impact of single family aggregators • Current health of the housing and single family rental markets • Market maturation and product availability • Evaluating housing cycles and how you think the single family rental strategy will perform • Market changes during the last year • Impact of Class “A” rental levels on single family rental demand • What is the outlook for rental inflation? Do you expect rental inflation to decelerate given the increased market share of single family rentals? • Is the increased rental demand fleeting or representative of a secular shift in homeownership/fallout from the over-buying of homes during the crisis? • How will single family rental market perform when there is a downtown? • Impact of owners moving back into black • When Ben Bernanke sneezes REITs get a cold: What is the Fed going to do? How will it impact the market? • Vampire REOs and zombie foreclosures • Are the seeds of the next housing recession already planted?
                            




Dennis Cisterna, Chief Revenue Officer, INVESTABILITY (Moderator)
Michael Simonsen, CEO, ALTOS RESEARCH
Rick Sharga, Executive Vice President, AUCTION.COM
Mark Fleming, Chief Economist, FIRST AMERICAN
Christopher Clothier, Partner/VP Sales & Marketing, MEMPHIS INVEST GP, DALLAS INVEST, HOUSTON INVEST
Jamie Woodwell, VP - Commercial Real Estate Research, MORTGAGE BANKERS ASSOCIATION
Walter 'Wally' Charnoff, CEO, INVESTABILITY




1:57 AM  The Public President/CEO Panel… What have you been doing the Last Six Months? 


                            • What part of the market are you targeting? • The going public experience • You can only buy so well and lease so well… How are you pulling off the operational side? • The next market you are looking to enter is… • How is price and interest rate appreciation impacting your strategy? • Acquisition strategy • Would you buy a large portfolio from a market you aren’t currently in? • Are you working with not-for-profits and local operators • Leverage plans what is the investment strategy? • How do you see the next year playing out? • Will this work as a long-term business model? Are there enough assets to continue to aggregate and rent out on a profitable basis? • Are we seeing the emergence of any industry reporting standards? • Are mergers in the horizon?
                            




Beth O'Brien, Chief Executive Officer, COLONY AMERICAN FINANCE (Moderator)
Stephen Schmitz, CEO, AMERICAN RESIDENTIAL PROPERTIES
Patrick Whelan, President, DECLAN, LTD.
Chad Carpenter, Chairman & CEO, REVEN CAPITAL, LLC
Doug Brien, Co-CEO & Co-Founder, MYND




1:57 AM  Refreshments Courtesy of: 









1:57 AM  Evaluating the Long-term Debt Market for Operators 


                            • How have the market changes over the past year impacted your financing strategy? • Increasing competition for deals and its affect • Growth assumptions • Are you financing build-for-rental? • Why have you chosen to be involved as a lender or equity provider? Why do you do, what you do? • Do you look to share on the upside? • What is your lending specialty? What are some key factors when you are looking to finance a project? • Time needed from origination to funding • Lending on stabilized (leased) properties vs. unstabilized(vacant) properties • Transparency and integrity
                            




Dennis Cisterna, Chief Revenue Officer, INVESTABILITY (Moderator)
John Beacham, President, B2R FINANCE
Todd Sammann, Principal, COLONY CAPITAL, LLC
Randy Reiff, Chief Executive Officer, FIRSTKEY LENDING, LLC
Rob Bloemker, Co-Founder, FIVE TEN CAPITAL
Dan Flanigan, Chair, Real Estate & Financial Services Department, POLSINELLI




Please Choose Track ‘A’ or B’





1:57 AM  The Valuation Process 


                            • The technology • Current cap rates • Discount to market values • Appreciation vs. cash flow expectation • Using automatic vs. inspection vs. appraisals • BPOs and other 3rd-party evaluations: What is their role? • Replacement and land value • Interest rates today and tomorrow • Rehab impact • Are you willing to pay more at an auction than other acquisition channels? • Lender vs. unit owner valuation • Valuing for flippers vs. keepers • Foreclosure discount or REO Haircut
                            




Jordan Kavana, Founder & CEO, TRANSCENDENT INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT (Moderator)
Michael Heid, Executive Vice President & Managing Director, ALLIANT INSURANCE SERVICES, INC.
Noel Christopher, SVP Business Development, RENTERS WAREHOUSE
Rob Walker, Managing Director, LPS APPLIED ANALYTICS
John Murray, President, CTO, REALTY PILOT, LLC




1:57 AM  Rehab/On-Going Maintenance 


                            • What is your rehab strategy for initial purposes? For re-rentals? • Partial vs. full rehab… What are the decision points? • In-house vs. 3rd-party • Tracking maintenance • Financing rehabilitation • What is your rehab costs and practices of “A”-“D” homes? • What is needed for occupied vs. abandoned homes • Flipping vs. keeping homes: What is your budget?
                            




Bradley Trapnell, SVP Business Development, HOMESTAR PROPERTY SOLUTIONS (Moderator)
Steven Helser, Chief Executive Officer, ASONS
Terry Sadowski, Chief Marketing Officer, ASSURANT FIELD ASSET SERVICES
Mike Bednarski, Managing Partner, BROOME CAPITAL, LLC
Christian Broadwell, CEO, REALTY PILOT, LLC
Samuel Tucci, VP, Business Operations, U.S. BEST REPAIR SERVICE, INC.




1:57 AM  Modeling the Investment & Performance Data of the Market 


                            • Rental income • Stress testing under different interest rate scenarios • Impact of the apartment rental market • Home prices • NPL performance • Early entrants, exits and their returns • Measuring property management performance • Key operating metrics that drive business models • How critical is rental growth? Role of inflation • Remodel return expectation • Are there differences in how players treat capital reserves? • Will operating expenses initially be understated due to upfront CAPX and the nature of the renter (lower initial turnover rate resulting in deferred maintenance)?
                            




Robert Antonio, Founder & President, ANTONIO FINANCIAL GROUP (Moderator)
Jonathan Philips, Managing Director, ANKA FUNDS
Christopher Clothier, Partner/VP Sales & Marketing, MEMPHIS INVEST GP, DALLAS INVEST, HOUSTON INVEST
Keith Dunkin, Senior Vice President, REALPAGE, INC.
John Knab, Managing Director, AMERICAS HOUSING ALLIANCE




1:57 AM  Day One Programming Concludes 





1:57 AM  Golf Tourney 


                            The Single Family Golf Outing will be on the JW Marriott Camelback Golf Club at the JW Marriott Camelback Inn. The outing will begin at 12:45pm sharp with a shotgun start, scramble play. All levels of players are welcome to play.A box lunch will be provided for all those who sign up.All conference registrants who would like to golf will have a $189 registration fee. All registrations are subject to IMN approval and are restricted to those attending the conference.All golfers must be registered and paid prior to the event. No exceptions will be made. Please be aware that space is limited and golfers are registered on a first-come, first-served basis. All of those who are interested should call Marva Massiah at (212) 901-0506 to register and complete payment. Please note that this payment is non-refundable. Registrants will not have a confirmed space in the tournament until payment is made to Marva.If you need to rent clubs, please let Ashley Roseman at IMN know via email whether you will need right or left handed clubs (aroseman@imn.org). Payment for club rentals is taken care of on site, just prior to the tournament. You will have the option to pay for your clubs at the course prior to the tournament, or charge the cost of renting clubs to your hotel room. The cost of club rental is $40 each, plus tax. The cost of shoe rental is $20.Requests to play together can be sent to Ashley Roseman. IMN handles all pairings and cannot guarantee that all requests will be met. All pairings are final. The golf outing is designed to accommodate all levels of skill.
                            






1:57 AM  Welcoming Reception Courtesy of: 









Thursday, December 5th, 2013


8:00 AM  Breakfast Courtesy of: 









1:57 AM  Impact on the Local Housing Markets When the Aggregators Come to Town 


                            • Price rises… How much? How much of the increase on prices is due to actual economic recovery or funds competing for very few properties in market • As the supply of rentals increases is the price remaining steady? • Are mini bubbles forming? • Long term exits…What will happen when everyone looks to sell at the same time? Will everyone sell? When will they sell? • Do aggregators mostly buy through auctions? Does this result in prices being bid up for this channel? How does this impact other channels? • Is there still a foreclosure discount or REO Haircut
                            




Kelly Johnson, National Sales Manager, ASONS  (Moderator)
Gregor Watson, Founder & Chief Investment Officer, 643 CAPITAL MANAGEMENT
Hanqing Zhou, Director – Housing Analysis and Research, FREDDIE MAC
Alex Sifakis, President, JWB REAL ESTATE CAPITAL
Daren Blomquist, Vice President, REALTYTRAC




1:57 AM  Opportunity/Hedge Fund Aggregator Panel: Are your Treating this as a Trade or New Market? 


                            As prices have risen and funding costs decrease for public market entrants is this market becoming less attractive for private market players? Are fund changing their practices to effectively compete? Other issues will include…• Why stay private? • Investment strategy and returns you are seeing vs. expecting • How are you handling the operation side of the equation? • What is your expected hold period? • Will this market ultimately be a retail or institutional market? • What type of returns are you targeting and how does that break out by home price appreciation (HPA) vs. cash yield? • Market target: price point vs. location vs. renter profile vs. rehab • What behavior do you expect on the part of the large players, mid-tier funds, and smaller groups over the next year or beyond? • In evaluating the economics of the business, what are the key factors?
                            




Jade Rahmani, Director- Single-Family REITs, KEEFE, BRUYETTE & WOODS, INC. (Moderator)
Robert Vahradian, Senior Managing Director, GTIS PARTNERS
Benjamin Hellweg, Head of Acquisitions, HOME PARTNERS OF AMERICA
Mitch Siegler, Senior Managing Director & Co-Founder, PATHFINDER PARTNERS, LLC
Oliver Chang, Co-Founder and Managing Director, SYLVAN ROAD CAPITAL
Jordan Kavana, Founder & CEO, TRANSCENDENT INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT




10:00 AM  Refreshments Courtesy of the Silver Sponsors 





Please Choose Track ‘A’ or B’





1:57 AM  An Overall Approach to Maintaining Asset Value & Making the Operation Side Work, Cost Effectively: Metrics, Benchmarks & Technology 


                            • Cost of renovation • Timeframe from closing to renovation to lease • Vacancy, turnover rate and associated costs • Average rents • Annual capital maintenance • Property management fees • Headcount and what they do •What is the optimal timing of CAPX spend? Front load or evenly distribute? Are there observable best practices? • Does it pay to fix up the neighborhood?
                            




Jeff Pintar, President, PINTAR INVESTMENT COMPANY, LLC (Moderator)
Ben Walls, Direction of Business Development, VIP REAL ESTATE INVESTOR.COM
Michael Breese, Managing Director, PINPOINT EQUITY GROUP
Blair Schrum, CEO, SES INSURANCE BROKERAGE SERVICES, INC.
Jon Fogg, COO, VISION EQUITY




1:57 AM  How is Home Price Appreciation Impacting the Market? 


                            • Rental growth vs. property prices • Paying up for properties • Markets with foreign buyers vs. those without • Job growth • How does appreciation alter many of the assumptions and expectations, around projected yield and return • Exit strategy • Dropping out of the market • Impact on flippers • Hyper home price appreciation” and its impact • Rent assumptions: How much growth can you assume without making an *** out of you and me?
                            




Lorenz Schwarz, Chief Operating Officer, GREEN RIVER CAPITAL (Moderator)
Mark Fleming, Chief Economist, FIRST AMERICAN
Alex Sifakis, President, JWB REAL ESTATE CAPITAL
Christopher Clothier, Partner/VP Sales & Marketing, MEMPHIS INVEST GP, DALLAS INVEST, HOUSTON INVEST




1:15 PM  Securitizing Rental Streams: Blackstone & Beyond 


                            • Current conduit/credit facility availability and terms • Investor interest • The unrated deal • Comparisons vs. home or commercial mortgage securitizations • How much leverage does securitization add to your operation? • Costs to issuer • Updates on rating agency concerns • NPL securitizations and REO-to-Rentals
                            




Michael Dryden, Managing Director, CREDIT SUISSE (Moderator)
Carl Bell, Managing Director & Deputy Chief Investment Officer, AMUNDI SMITH BREEDEN
Ryan Stark, Managing Director, DEUTSCHE BANK
David Lefkowitz, Managing Director, JP MORGAN SECURITIES LLC
Daniel Rubock, Senior Vice President, MOODY'S INVESTORS SERVICE, INC.
Brian Grow, Managing Director – RMBS/SFR/ABS, MORNINGSTAR CREDIT RATINGS, LLC
Stephen Blevit, Partner, SIDLEY AUSTIN LLP




1:57 AM  Acquisition Technology, Due Diligence & Valuation 


                            This session will discuss the plumbing behind how you make the decision to acquire a property and include:• How much time and energy can be saved by only bidding on properties that fit your criteria exactly? • The math behind the models • Which off-the-shelf systems are you using? • Custom systems and what they have • Beyond the MLS • Examining market-, neighborhood- and property-level information
                            




Robert Lee, Managing Director, SYLVAN ROAD CAPITAL, LLC (Moderator)
Jeffrey Brock, CEO and Founder, KEY PROPERTY SERVICES
Rob Walker, Managing Director, LPS APPLIED ANALYTICS
Gregory Rand, CEO, OWNAMERICA
Michael Hermosillo, Director of Operations, PRECISION BOOMERANG
Walter 'Wally' Charnoff, CEO, INVESTABILITY
Colin Wiel, Co-Founder and Co-CEO, MYND




1:57 AM  Evaluating Secondary Single Aggregation Markets 


                            • Where is the rental demand? • Are there any below replacement cost markets left? • Northeastern markets: Can you succeed in the Boston-New York-DC corridor • Are all secondary markets scalable? • Foreclosure protection laws to be aware of • What Inning are we in? Examining the traditional hot single family markets
                            




Haendel St. Juste, Executive Director- Research, MORGAN STANLEY (Moderator)
Gregory Rand, CEO, OWNAMERICA
Jake Adger, Chief Economist, REALTYTRAC
Alexander Philips, CEO, TWINROCK PARTNERS, LLC
Stephen Rosenburgh, President & Chief Executive Officer, US DEVELOPMENTS




1:57 AM  Public Buyer Panel: What Makes you a Buyer? 


                            • Do you believe in the story? • How do you value these companies? • Revenue and expense keys • Relative value vs. other REITs • What factors do you look at? Balance sheet debt? Vacancy level? • Accounting treatment
                            




Ron Mass, Managing Principal, ALMITAS CAPITAL (Moderator)
Jeffrey Hinkle, CIO, ZINKLE HOLDINGS
Dave Bragg, Managing Director, GREEN STREET ADVISORS
Peter Martin, Managing Director, Equity Research, JMP SECURITIES LLC
James Graff, Co-Head of Real Estate Investment Banking, RAYMOND JAMES & ASSOCIATES




1:00 PM  Luncheon Courtesy of: 


Featuring Local Market Luncheon Roundtables (Arizona, Atlanta, The Carolinas, Chicago/Midwest, Florida, Las Vegas, Southern California, Texas)During lunch we will have several tables that you can sign up for at registration to meet others interested in these markets.
                            










1:57 AM  What is your Overall Acquisition Strategy? New Takes on Traditional Channels and Alternative Sourcing Strategies 


As foreclosures wind down, auctions are so crowded that you can’t even get near the court house and markets become increasingly competitive and frothy it becomes of the utmost importance to find different ways to find product. This session will details some of those ways including• Locations you are in… Locations where you want to be... Markets you are looking to dispose product • Class “A-D”: What is your target? • Local entrepreneur portfolios • The perfect home size is… • Is the banking/ NPL channel dead? • Experiences with government portfolios • Portfolio diversification • How do you evaluate: Buy and refurb vs. purchase leased? • Are there condo deals still around? How about foreclosed single family communities? • Marketing to existing home owners • Home builders construction rental only communities and single units • Tax liens • Short sales • Eminent domain update • Investing in second mortgages
                            




Howard Steinberg, Managing Member, PBFS GROUP (Moderator)
Ashish Pandey, Chief Executive Officer, ALTISOURCE RESIDENTIAL
Amy Tait, Chairman & CEO, BROADSTONE REAL ESTATE, LLC
Matt Blank, Principal, BB LIVING
Greg Coleman, Co-Founder & Managing Partner, REVEST ASSET MANAGEMENT
Jeffrey McHenry, EVP, ZVN PROPERTIES INC.




1:57 AM  Bank/NPL Servicer Workouts, Dispositions and Buyers Plenary 


                            • What is your REO/note disposition pipeline looking like? What is your preferred disposition method? • Current pricing: Is discounting yesterday’s news? If the property doesn’t sell, what is your price reduction strategy? • Impact of homeowners’ bill of rights in California and other such legislation • Use of short sales or deeds-in-lieu • FHA “Claim without conveyance of title” program • How are you complying with disclosure requirements? • Is the legal system allowing efficient processing or do you have a backlog?
                            




Chris Friis, Chief Credit Officer, THE BANCORP (Moderator)
Joseph Schillinger, Managing Member, EAST ROCK FINANCIAL, LLC
Jason West, Executive Vice President, PINNACLE FINANCIAL PARTNERS
Robert Madden, , TRINITY FINANCIAL SERVICES
Steven Shiller, Senior Vice President, WINGSPAN PORTFOLIO ADVISORS




1:57 AM  Short-Term Finance/Lines of Credit Best Practices 


                            • What is the structure looking like? • What are lenders looking for? • Terms • Facility uses • Pooling across different portfolios • Is it a better time to go long? • Line leverage • Facilities from the small community banks vs. Wall Street vs. the funds • Expense and loss risk of facilities • Eye on securitization
                            




Gene Clark, President, 5 ARCH (Moderator)
Gregor Watson, Founder & Chief Investment Officer, 643 CAPITAL MANAGEMENT
Thad Meyer, CFO, REVEN HOUSING REIT
John Beacham, President, B2R FINANCE
Randal Johnson, Director, DEUTSCHE BANK
Eric Atlas, Managing Director, FIRSTKEY LENDING, LLC




1:57 AM  Working With Municipalities and States: Politics, Regulations and Code Issues 


                            • What do municipalities look for from the home rental companies? • How have cities adapted to home rentals? • What repairs do local government require before REO is placed in service as rental? • How does local government view Housing Choice vouchers/Section 8 subsidized rentals? • What type and level of code enforcement should REO purchasers expect to encounter? • How does local government deal with “walkaways”… vacant but not in foreclosure?
                            




Eric Workman, Vice President of Sales and Marketing, MACK COMPANIES (Moderator)
Fabrizio Santoro, Founder, ALTO INVESTMENTS
JoAnn Velde, Deputy Director Housing Inspection Services, CITY OF MINNEAPOLIS
Tim Boling, Deputy Director, CITY OF PHOENIX
Jack Bevier, Partner, THE DOMINION GROUP




1:57 AM  Refreshments Courtesy of the Silver Sponsors 





1:57 AM  Managing the Customer… Your Tenant 


                            • Keys to effective customer service • Setting up your call center • Handling incoming inquiries • Tracking repair and maintenance inquiries • Establishing and implementing service standards and response times • Any new landlord/tenant laws to be concerned with?
                            




